The paper deals with secure transmissions in wireless channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) and multiple-antenna-eavesdropper (MIMOME) systems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on statistical channel state information and optimization problems suggests that it may also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
